Youth Sports Federation of Nigeria (YSFON) has commended the Governor of Kano State Alhaji Umar Ganduje for endorsing his deputy who equally doubles as National President of (YSFON) Dr Yusuf Nasiru Gawuna for the governorship seat. He made this known during a stakeholders meeting of the ruling All Progressives Congress (APC) in the state, held at Africa House, Government House, Kano, Describing Gawuna as a complete gentleman, “who knows what is right and what is wrong. He is reliable and loyal.”   Awoniyi nets brace to end season with 20 goals     Wydad qualify for CAF Champions League final     Osimhen pockets ₦114m for helping Napoli qualify for…   In a statement by the body’s national secretary Patrick Okpavuehre the Federation said it is highly elated by the honour done its President noting that they’re sure Gawuna will continue with the good legacies of his principal and carry out programmes that will further uplift the state. “We at YSFON are very excited with this development because it shows how cordial our National President has worked with his boss and we don’t have any doubt in our minds that as a tested technocrat, Gawuna will bring his wealth of experience to play when he eventually takes over government next year and we pray that the Almighty Allah will see him through in the primaries, electoral campaigns and the election proper” the statement concluded.